{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id441cc3fe-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s841"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"841"},"text":"§ 841.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Credit for foreign taxes","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The taxes imposed by foreign countries or possessions of the United States shall be allowed as a credit against the tax of a domestic insurance company subject to the tax imposed by section 801 or 831, to the extent provided in the case of a domestic corporation in section 901 (relating to foreign tax credit). For purposes of the preceding sentence (and for purposes of applying section 906 with respect to a foreign corporation subject to tax under this subchapter), the term “taxable income” as used in section 904 means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id441cc3ff-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s841/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of the tax imposed by section 801, the life insurance company taxable income (as defined in section 801(b)), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id441cc400-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s841/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of the tax imposed by section 831, the taxable income (as defined in section 832(a)).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id441cc401-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/267"},"text":"68A Stat. 267","children":[